Class ZipkinLoggerConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mulesoft.consulting.zipkinloggerconnector.ZipkinLoggerConnector

  • @Connector(name="zipkin-logger",
           friendlyName="Zipkin Logger",
           minMuleVersion="3.8.0")
public class ZipkinLoggerConnector
extends Object
    Zipkin is a distributed tracing system. It helps gather timing data needed to troubleshoot latency problems in microservice architectures. It manages both the collection and lookup of this data. Zipkinâ€™s design is based on the Google Dapper paper.
    Author:
    michaelhyatt
    See Also:
    Zipkin, Zipkin Github repo, Zipkin brave Java client library, Dapper paper

public SpanData createNewTrace(@Optional @Default(value="#[]")

        Creates new synchronous trace and new parent span. Requires subsequent finish-span element to complete and publish the trace.
        Parameters:
        logMessage - Logged message that will be added as one of the tags with name "log"
        additionalTags - additional map of tags to add as Map
        ServerOrClientSpanType - indicator whether the span is logged as SERVER or CLIENT brave.span.Kind
        spanName - name of the span

      • joinExternalSpan

        @Processor
public SpanData joinExternalSpan(@Optional @Default(value="#[]")
                                            String logMessage,
                                            @Optional @Default(value="#[]")
                                            Map<String,String> additionalTags,
                                            @Default(value="SERVER")
                                            brave.Span.Kind ServerOrClientSpanType,
                                            @Default(value="myspan")
                                            String spanName,
                                            @Default(value="#[message.inboundProperties.\'x-b3-spanid\']")
                                            String spanId,
                                            @Default(value="#[message.inboundProperties.\'x-b3-parentspanid\']")
                                            String parentSpanId,
                                            @Default(value="#[message.inboundProperties.\'x-b3-traceid\']")
                                            String traceId,
                                            @Optional @Default(value="#[message.inboundProperties.\'x-b3-sampled\']")
                                            String sampled,
                                            @Optional @Default(value="#[message.inboundProperties.\'x-b3-flags\']")
                                            String flags)
        Creates new span and adds it to the externally originated parent span known through its B3 propagation attributes. Requires subsequent finish-span element to complete and publish the trace.
        Parameters:
        logMessage - Logged message that will be added as one of the tags with name "log"
        additionalTags - additional map of tags to add as Map
        ServerOrClientSpanType - indicator whether the span is logged as SERVER or CLIENT brave.span.Kind
        spanName - name of the span
        spanId - spanId of external span to join
        parentSpanId - parentSpanId of external span to join
        traceId - traceId of external span to join
        sampled - sampled value ("1" or "0") of external span to join
        flags - flags (debug - "1" or "0") of external span to join
        Returns:
        payload with SpanData POJO
